The '''Rebel Legion''' is a worldwide costuming group of ''[[Star Wars]]'' fans in [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance]] costume that often participates in charity work and community service. Following its formation in [[2000]], it has often worked with [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney]] and [[Lucasfilm]], as well as other costuming groups such as the [[501st Legion (fan organization)|501st Legion]]. Several members of the Rebel Legion portrayed background characters in the themed attraction ''[[Star Tours: The Adventures Continue]]'', and the organization has been the subject of numerous [[StarWars.com]] articles.

==History==
===Founding and purpose===
[[File:RebelLegion.jpg|thumb|left|300px|Rebel Legion members]]
The Rebel Legion is a worldwide costuming group of ''[[Star Wars]]'' fans in [[Alliance to Restore the Republic|Rebel Alliance]] costume.<ref name="RL-FAQ" /> It was founded in [[January]] [[2000]] by Tony Troxell, Richard Fairbrother, Doug Fesko, and Ed O'Connell.<ref name="RL-WWA" /> often participating in charity work and community service. The Rebel Legion was initially formed in reaction to the [[501st Legion (fan organization)|501st Legion]] fan organization&mdash;another costuming group&mdash;and both organizations regularly work together with shared members. In the time since its formation, the Rebel Legion has grown to become one of [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney]] and [[Lucasfilm Ltd.|Lucasfilm's]] preferred costuming groups. Some Rebel Legion costumes are submitted for Lucasfilm approval for feedback after their construction.<ref name="RL-FAQ" />

The Rebel Legion's commanding officer is elected from its membership and serves as its figurehead and spokesperson, operating as the organization's primary point of contact for Lucasfilm. As of [[2024]], the Rebel Legion's commanding officer is Anthony Wilson.<ref name="RL-CS">{{WebCite|url=https://rebellegion.com/command-staff|text=Command Staff &ndash; Rebel Legion|archivedate=20240610025346}}</ref> Member costumes include Jedi, clone troopers, rebel pilots, rebel troopers, rebel commanders, royalty and senators, smugglers, and creatures.<ref name="RL-WWA" />

===''Star Tours: The Adventures Continue''===
[[File:StarTours_II_poster.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Rebel Legion members participated in the creation of ''Star Tours: The Adventures Continue''.]]
In [[2010]], Lucasfilm asked several members of the 501st Legion&mdash;some of whom were also part of the Rebel Legion&mdash;to participate in a photo shoot for the upcoming themed attraction ''[[Star Tours: The Adventures Continue]]''. In [[August]] of that year, several members attended the recording session, including [[Star Wars Blog|''Star Wars'' Blog]] contributor [[Lawrence Green]], who was a member of the organizations.<ref name="StarTours">{{SW|url=news/how-the-501st-and-rebel-legions-became-part-of-star-tours|text=How the 501st and Rebel Legions Became Part of Star Tours}}</ref>

One other member of Rebel Legion&mdash;[[Rob Howe]]&mdash;portrayed a [[snowspeeder]] [[pilot]] on [[Comm unit|comms]] on the [[Water|ice]] [[planet]] [[Hoth]]. Other members of the group portayed various background characters throughout the attraction in silhouette form.<ref name="StarTours" /> The attraction ultimately first debuted at [[Wikipedia:Walt Disney World|Walt Disney World]] in [[Wikipedia:Orlando|Orlando]], [[Wikipedia:Florida|Florida]] on [[May 20]], [[2011]].<ref name="StarToursReturns">{{WebCite|url=http://www.theforce.net/latestnews/story/Star_Tours_Returns_Starting_May_20th_136170.asp|text=Star Tours Returns Starting May 20th|author=Eeric Geller|date=2011-01-18|archivedate=20190729153331}}</ref> The Rebel Legion's contributions to the project were were later published in a [[StarWars.com]] interview with Green conducted by author [[Amy Ratcliffe]], which was published on [[August 29]], [[2014]].<ref name="StarTours" />

===Futher work===
[[File:Stephen Stanton.jpg|thumb|left|250px|Stephen Stanton is an honorary member of the Rebel Legion.]]
The costuming group was also featured amongst several others in a [[Celebration Europe II]] lead-up video done by [[Ashley Eckstein]], the voice actor for [[Jedi]] [[Padawan]] [[Ahsoka Tano]] in the ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]'' animated television series.<ref name="Ashley">{{SW|url=video/star-wars-fan-groups-celebrating-a-galaxy-far-far-away|text=Star Wars Fan Groups: Celebrating A Galaxy Far, Far Away}}</ref> [[Mark Newbold]], a contributor to ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' and the ''[[Star Wars: Build the Millennium Falcon]]'' magazines, is an Honorary Friend of the Rebel Legion.<ref name="Newbold">{{SW|url=news/contributor/mnewbold|text=Mark Newbold}}</ref>

Members of Rebel Legion was at [[Celebration VI]] in [[2012]],<ref name="Celebration VI">{{SW|url=news/swcvi-this-will-be-a-day-long-remembered|text=SWCVI: This Will Be A Day Long Remembered|nolive=1}}</ref> as well as Long Beach Comic Con the same year, inducting [[Stephen Stanton]]&mdash;a voice actor from ''Star Wars: The Clone Wars''&mdash;as an honorary member.<ref name="LBCC">{{SW|url=news/long-beach-comic-con-i-should-have-expected-to-find-you-here|text=Long Beach Comic Con: I Should Have Expected to Find You Here|nolive=1}}</ref> Rebel Legion maintained a presence at [[Wikipedia:San Diego Comic-Con|San Diego Comic-Con]]<ref name="SDCC 2013">{{SW|url=news/troopers-and-rebels-behind-the-magic-at-sdcc-2013|text=Troopers and Rebels: Behind the Magic at SDCC 2013|nolive=1}}</ref> and the [[Wikipedia:WonderCon|WonderCon]] conventions in 2013,<ref name="Wonderment">{{SW|url=news/wondercon-wonderment-2013|text=WonderCon Wonderment 2013!|nolive=1}}</ref> both of which had respective StarWars.com articles.<ref name="SDCC 2013" /><ref name="Wonderment" /> Also in 2013, the Rebel Legion worked alongside several Disney employees to volunteer for Operation Gratitude, which was later documented on StarWars.com.<ref name="Gratitude">{{SW|url=news/trooping-for-the-troops|text=Trooping for the Troops|nolive=1}}</ref>

===Post-canon reset===
In [[2014]], Rebel Legion maintained a presence at the WonderCon alongside the 501st Legion, which was included alongside a list of the event's other ''Star Wars''-related programming in an article on StarWars.com.<ref name="WonderCon">{{SW|url=news/vanessa-marshall-the-galaxys-newest-rebel-is-heading-to-wondercon|text=Vanessa Marshall, the Galaxy's Newest Rebel, Is Heading to WonderCon}}</ref> An article further detailing the organization's presence at the event was published by Green on [[April 29]] of that year.<ref name="WonderCon-Green">{{SW|url=news/wondercon-2014-the-501st-and-rebel-legion-in-full-force|text=WonderCon 2014: The 501st and Rebel Legion In Full Force|nolive=1}}</ref>

[[File:RebelLegion-TLJ.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Several Rebel Legion members were invited to the premiere of ''Star Wars'': Episode VIII ''The Last Jedi''.]]
Rebel Legion and 501st Legion members Alexina Duncan<ref name="Costuming">{{SW|url=news/galactic-costuming-alexina-duncans-amazing-hera-syndulla-cosplay|text=Galactic Costuming: Alexina Duncan's Amazing Hera Syndulla Cosplay}}</ref> and Emily Schram<ref name="GalacticCostuming">{{SW|url=news/galactic-costuming-emily-schram-cool-captain-rex-cosplay|text=Galactic Costuming: Emily Schram's Cool Captain Rex Cosplay}}</ref> were interviewed as part of Ratcliffe's "Galactic Costuming" series of articles highlighting members of fan costuming groups worldwide for an article on StarWars.com, which were published on [[August 17]], [[2017]],<ref name="Costuming" /> and [[January 3]], [[2018]], respectively.<ref name="GalacticCostuming" />In [[December]] 2017, members of Rebel Legion were invited to the red carpet premiere of the 2017 [[sequel trilogy]] film [[Star Wars: Episode VIII The Last Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VIII ''The Last Jedi'']]. They met several cast and crew while dressed in costumes of new characters from the film, and some parts of their interviews were included in a StarWars.com article by [[Dan Brooks]].<ref name="TLJ">{{SW|url=news/these-star-wars-the-last-jedi-cosplayers-from-the-red-carpet-premiere-are-most-impressive|text=These ''Star Wars: The Last Jedi'' Cosplayers from the Red Carpet Premiere Are Most Impressive}}</ref>

One member of the Rebel Legion&mdash;Lisa Liebig&mdash;was interviewed at [[Celebration Anaheim (2022)|Celebration Anaheim]] in [[2022]] as part of a set of fan interviews conducted for a StarWars.com article published on [[May 29]] of that year.<ref name="SWCA">{{SW|url=news/swca-2022-fan-interviews|text=SWCA 2022: Fans Share the Joy of ''Star Wars'' Celebration Anaheim 2022}}</ref> Also during May of that year, Rebel Legion and several other fan costuming groups worked alongside Lucasfilm to raise money for [[Wikipedia:Starlight Children's Foundation|Starlight Children's Foundation]], raising thirty thousand dollars. Their efforts were mentioned in [[June 9]], 2022, episode of ''[[This Week! in Star Wars]]'' on theofficial ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[Wikipedia:YouTube|YouTube]] channel, hosted by [[Kristin Baver]].<ref name="ThisWeek">{{ThisWeek|9JAFxVEiLAU|Obi-Wan Kenobi Leaves Tatooine, Deborah Chow and Moses Ingram Talk Reva, and More!|sw_url=video/obi-wan-kenobi-leaves-tatooine-deborah-chow-and-moses-ingram-talk-reva-and-more}}</ref>

